The paper deals with 3D point cloud registration, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The paper proposes a new algorithm for solving the combinatorial problem of matching with pairwise constraints, which is a fundamental problem in many areas of computer science, including computer vision, machine learning, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves graph theory and algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper proposes an efficient algorithm for solving a combinatorial problem, which could also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves optimization and robust estimation, which could also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
